{"kanda":6,"sarga":14,"description":"","verses":[{"v":1,"dev":"निशाचरेन्द्रस्यनिशम्यवाक्यंसकुम्भकर्णस्यचगर्जितानि ।विभीषणोराक्षसराजमुख्यमुवाचवाक्यंहितमर्थयुक्तम्","trans":"On hearing the statement of the Lord of Rakshasas and roaring of Kumbhakarna, looking at Ravana the king of Rakshasas, Vibheeshana said these good words appropriate of a noble person.","words":[{"d":"विभीषणः","m":"Vibheeshana"},{"d":"निशाचरेन्द्रस्य:","m":"the Lord of Rakshasas"},{"d":"वाक्यम्","m":"statement"},{"d":"कुम्भकर्णस्य:","m":"Kumbhakarna's"},{"d":"गर्जितानि:","m":"roaring"},{"d":"निशम्य:","m":"looking at"},{"d":"हितम्","m":"good"},{"d":"अर्थयुक्तम्","m":"meaningful"},{"d":"वाक्यम्","m":"statement"},{"d":"राक्षसराजमुख्यम्","m":"king of Rakshasas"},{"d":"उवाच:","m":"said."}]},{"v":2,"dev":"न्तरभोगराशिश्चिन्ताविषस्सुस्मिततीक्ष्णदंष्ट्रः ।पञ्चाङ्गुलीपञ्चशिरोऽतिकायस्सीतामहाहिस्तवकेनराजन्","trans":"\"O king Why have you desired Sita who has snake hood at her bosom, has poison of grief, has sharp fangs behind her gentle smile and has five fingers of her palm as five heads of snake called Sita?\"","words":[{"d":"राजन्","m":"O king"},{"d":"बाह्वन्तरभोगराशिः","m":"who has the hood at her bosom"},{"d":"चिन्ताविषः","m":"poison of grief"},{"d":"सुस्मिततीक्ष्णदंष्ट्रः","m":"has sharp fangs behind her gentle smile"},{"d":"पञ्चाङ्गुलीपञ्चशिरोऽतिकायः","m":"has her five fingers of the palm like five heads of snake"},{"d":"सीतामहाहिः","m":"snake called Sita"},{"d":"केन:","m":"why"},{"d":"तववृतः","m":"you desired."}]},{"v":3,"dev":"यावन्नलङ्कांसमभिद्रवन्तिवलीमुखाःपर्वतकूटमात्राः ।दष्ट्रायुधाश्चैवनखायुधाश्चप्रदीयतांदाशरथायमैथिली","trans":"\"Before the monkeys of mountain like form whose teeth and claws are like weapons reach Lanka, give away Mythili to Rama.\"","words":[{"d":"पर्वतकूटमात्राः","m":"of mountain like form"},{"d":"दंष्ट्रायुधाः","m":"who have teeth as weapons"},{"d":"नखायुधाश्च:","m":"and claws as weapons"},{"d":"वलीमुखाः","m":"monkeys"},{"d":"यावत्","m":"all of them"},{"d":"लङ्काम्","m":"to Lanka"},{"d":"नसमभिद्रवन्ति:","m":"before reaching"},{"d":"दाशरथाय:","m":"to Rama"},{"d":"मैथिली:","m":"Mythili"},{"d":"प्रदीयताम्","m":"give away."}]},{"v":4,"dev":"यावन्नगृह्णन्तिशिरांसिबाणारामेरिताराक्षसपुङ्गवानाम् ।वज्रोपमावायुसमानवेगाःप्रदीयतांदाशरथायमैथिली","trans":"\"Give away Mythili to Rama before he releases arrows like that of thunder bolt with the speed of wind and take away the heads of the leader.\"","words":[{"d":"वज्रोसमाः","m":"equal to thunderbolt"},{"d":"वायुसमानवेगाः","m":"speed of wind"},{"d":"रामेरिताः","m":"released by Rama"},{"d":"बाणाः","m":"arrows"},{"d":"राक्षसपुङ्गवानाम्","m":"leaders of Rakshasas"},{"d":"शिरांसि:","m":"heads"},{"d":"यावत्","m":"l"},{"d":"नगृह्णन्ति:","m":"take away"},{"d":"मैथिली:","m":"Mythili"},{"d":"दाशरथाय:","m":"to Rama son of Dasaratha"},{"d":"प्रदीयताम्","m":"give away."}]},{"v":5,"dev":"नकुम्भकर्णेन्द्रजितौचराजंस्तथामहापार्श्वमहोदरौवा ।निकुम्भकुम्भौचतथाऽतिकायःस्थातुंनशक्तायुधिराघवस्य","trans":"\"O King It will not be possible for either Kumbhakarna or Indrajith so also for Mahaparsva not even Mahodara, so also for Nikumbha or Kumbha and Athikaya to face Rama in combat.\"","words":[{"d":"राजन्","m":"O king"},{"d":"कुम्भकर्णेन्द्रजितौ:","m":"either Kumbhakarna or Indrajith"},{"d":"तथा:","m":"so also"},{"d":"महापार्श्वमहोदरौवा:","m":"Mahaparsva, Mahodara or"},{"d":"निकुम्भकुम्भौ:","m":"Nikumbha or Kumbha"},{"d":"तथा:","m":"so also"},{"d":"अतिकायः","m":"Athikaya"},{"d":"युधि:","m":"in combat"},{"d":"राघवस्य:","m":"at Raghava"},{"d":"स्थातुम्","m":"to face"},{"d":"शक्ता: न:","m":"not possible."}]},{"v":6,"dev":"जीवंस्तुरामस्यनमोक्ष्यसेत्वंगुप्तस्सवित्राप्यथवामरुद्भि: ।नवासवस्याङ्कगतोनमृत्योर्नभोनपाताळमनुप्रविष्टः","trans":"\"Rama's arrows will not leave you with life even if you are guarded by Sun or wind god, not even if you sit on the lap of Indra or death god or even if you enter the sky or under water.\"","words":[{"d":"त्वम्","m":"you"},{"d":"सवित्रा:","m":"Sun"},{"d":"अथवा:","m":"or else"},{"d":"मरुद्भि:","m":"eve