 welfare of the king, intent upon Dharma, artha and kama, thinking rightly and deeply, spoke these words on hearing Prahastha's words that were not good.","words":[{"d":"ततः","m":"then"},{"d":"राजहितानुकाङ्क्षी:","m":"desiring king's welfare"},{"d":"धर्मार्थकामेषु:","m":"dharma (righteousness) artha (material prosperity) and Kama (sensual desires)"},{"d":"निविष्टबुद्धि:","m":"thinking deeply and rightly"},{"d":"विभीषणः","m":"Vibheeshana"},{"d":"अहितम्","m":"that which is not good"},{"d":"प्रहस्तवाक्यम्","m":"Prahastha's word"},{"d":"निशम्य:","m":"hearing"},{"d":"महार्थम्","m":"well meaning"},{"d":"वचनम्","m":"words"},{"d":"बभाषे:","m":"spoke."}]},{"v":10,"dev":"प्रहस्त: राजाचमहोदरश्चत्वंकुम्भकर्णश्चयथाऽर्थजातम् ।ब्रवीतरामंप्रतितन्नशक्यंयथागतिस्स्वर्गमधर्मबुद्धेः","trans":"\"That which you intend to accomplish against Rama is not possible either for you or the king and even for Kumbhakarna and Mahodara, just as heaven is not obtained by the unrighteous people,\" said Vibheeshana.","words":[{"d":"प्रहस्त:","m":"Prahastha"},{"d":"राजाच:","m":"and king"},{"d":"महोदरश्च:","m":"Mahodara also"},{"d":"त्वम्","m":"you"},{"d":"कुम्भकर्णश्च:","m":"and Kumbhakarna"},{"d":"रामंप्रति:","m":"against Rama"},{"d":"अर्थजातम्","m":"intend to accomplish"},{"d":"यथा:","m":"just as"},{"d":"ब्रवीत:","m":"said"},{"d":"तत्","m":"that"},{"d":"अधर्मबुद्देः","m":"one who is not righteous"},{"d":"स्वर्गम्","m":"heaven"},{"d":"गतिः","m":"obtained"},{"d":"यथा","m":"so also"},{"d":"नशक्यम्","m":"not possible."}]},{"v":11,"dev":"वधस्तुरामस्यमयात्वयाचप्रहस्तसर्वैरपिराक्षसैर्वा ।कथंभवेदर्थविशारदस्यमहार्णवंतर्तुमिवाप्लवस्य","trans":"\"Prahastha How can you or me or all Rakshasas kill Rama who is knowledgeable of everything, just as one who is not swimming can cross the great ocean.\"","words":[{"d":"हस्त:","m":"Prahastha"},{"d":"मया:","m":"by me"},{"d":"त्वयाच:","m":"and by you"},{"d":"सर्वैः","m":"all"},{"d":"राक्षसैर्वा:","m":"by Rakshasas also"},{"d":"अर्थविशारदस्य:","m":"one who is knowledgeable of everything"},{"d":"रामस्य:","m":"Rama's"},{"d":"वधः","m":"killing"},{"d":"अप्लवस्य:","m":"not swimming"},{"d":"महार्णवम्","m":"great ocean"},{"d":"तर्तुम् इव:","m":"like crossing"},{"d":"कथम्","m":"how"},{"d":"भवेत्","m":"will it be possible."}]},{"v":12,"dev":"धर्मप्रधानस्यमहारथस्यइक्ष्वाकुवंशप्रभवस्यराज्ञः ।पुरोस्यदेवाश्चतथाविधस्यकृत्येषुशक्तस्यभवन्तिमूढा","trans":"\"One to whom righteousness is foremost, who is capable of fighting with eleven thousand warriors as charioteer, (like Dasaratha) who is a glorious scion of Ikshvaku dynasty, who is highly capable in war, in front of whom even gods got bewildered earlier. What can be done by you?\"","words":[{"d":"धर्मप्रधानस्य:","m":"one to whom righteousness alone is foremost"},{"d":"महारथस्य:","m":"a great charioteer"},{"d":"इक्ष्वाकुवंशप्रभवस्य:","m":"glorious son of Ikshvaku dynasty"},{"d":"कृत्येषु:","m":"in action"},{"d":"शक्तस्य:","m":"very capable"},{"d":"तथाविधस्य:","m":"in such acts राज्ञः by the king"},{"d":"अस्य:","m":"its"},{"d":"पुरः","m":"earlier"},{"d":"देवाश्च:","m":"even gods"},{"d":"मूढा:","m":"bewildered"},{"d":"भवन्ति:","m":"by you at present."}]},{"v":13,"dev":"तीक्ष्णानतायत्तवकङ्कपत्रादुरासदाराघवविप्रमुक्ताः ।भित्वाशरीरंप्रविशन्तिबाणाःप्रहस्ततेनैवविकत्थसेत्वम्","trans":"\"Prahastha Sharp arrows of Rama fixed with feathers of Kanka birds are dangerous arrows. They will tear your body and penetrate. What are you boasting yourself?\"","words":[{"d":"प्रहस्त:","m":"Prahastha"},{"d":"तीक्ष्णाः","m":"sharp"},{"d":"कङ्कपत्राः","m":"arrows fixed with feathers of kanka bird"},{"d":"दुरासदाः","m":"dangerous ones"},{"d":"राघवविप्रमुक्ताः","m":"released by Rama"},{"d":"बाणाः","m":"arrows"},{"d":"तवशरीरम्","m":"your body"},{"d":"भित्त्वा:","m":"tear"},{"d":"प्रविशन्ति:","m":"penetrate तावत् therefore"},{"d":"तेनैव:","m":"yourself"},{"d":"त्वम्","m":"your"},{"d":"विकत्थसे:","m":"boasting."}]},{"v":14,"dev":"भित्त्वानतावत्प्रविशन्तिकायंप्राणान्तिकास्तेऽशनितुल्यवेगाः ।शिताश्शराराघवविप्रमुक्ताःप्रहस्ततेनैवविकत्थसेत्वम्","trans":"\"Prahastha Before the lifethreatening sharp arrows which have the speed of a meteor released by Rama penetrate and tear your body, why are you boasting yourself?\"","words":[{"d":"प्रहस्त:","m":"Prahastha"},{"d":"राघवविप्रमुक्ताः","m":"released by Rama"},{"d":"प्राणान्तकाः","m":"those life threatening"},{"d":"अशनितुल्यवेगाः","m":"which have the speed of a meteor"},{"d":"शिताः","m":"sharp"},{"d":"शराः","m":"arrows"},{"d":"ते:","m":"your"},{"d":"कायम्","m":"body"},{"d":"भित्त्वा:","m":"tearing"},{"d":"नतावत् प्रविशन्ति:","m":"will not penetrate"},{"d":"तेनैव:","m":"yourself"},{"d":"त्वम्","m":"you"},{"d":"विकत्थसे:","m":"boasting."}]},{"v":15,"dev":"नरावणोनातिबलस्त्रिशीर्षोनकुम्भकर्णोऽस्यसुतोनिकुम्भः ।नचेन्द्रजिद्दाशरधिंप्रसोढुंत्वंवारणेशक्रसमंसमर्थ:।। 6.14.15।।","trans":"\"Either Ravana or exceptionally strong Trisirsha, or even Nikumbha son of Kumbahakarna, or Indrajith are not capable of opposing Rama who is equal to Indra in war. How can you?\"","words":[{"d":"शक्रसमम्","m":"equal to Indra"},{"d":"दाशरथिम्","m":"son of Dasaratha"},{"d":"रणे:","m":"in war"},{"d":"सोढुम्","m":"to oppose"},{"d":"रावणः","m":"Ravana"},{"d":"नसमर्थः","m":"not capable"},{"d":"अतिबलः","m":"exceptionally strong"},{"d":"त्रिशीर्षः","m":"Trisirsha"},{"d":"न:","m":"not"},{"d":"कुम्भकर्णस्य:","m":"Kumbhakarna's"},{"d":"सुतः","m":"son"},{"d":"निकुम्भः","m":"Nikumbha"},{"d":"न:","m":"not"},{"d":"इन्द्रजित्","m":"Indrajith"},{"d":"न:","m":"not possible"},{"d":"त्वंवा:","m":"how can you."}]},{"v":16,"dev":"देवान्तकोवापिनरान्तकोवातथातिकायोऽतिरथोमहात्मा ।आकम्पनश्चाद्रिसमानसारःस्थातुंनशक्तायुधिराघवस्य","trans":"\"Either by Devanthaka or Naranthaka, in the same way the great soul Athiratha or Akampana, who is of mountainlike size, will not be able to stand against Raghava in war.\"","words":[{"d":"देवान्तकोवापि:","m":"either Devanthaka"},{"d":"नरान्तकोवा:","m":"or Naranthaka"},{"d":"तथाअतिरधः","m":"in the same way Athiratha"},{"d":"महात्मा:","m":"great soul"},{"d":"अतिकायः","m":"Athikaya"},{"d":"अद्रिसमानसारः","m":"even if he is of mountain in size"},{"d":"अकम्पनश्च:","m":"like Akampana"},{"d":"राघवस्य:","m":"with Raghava"},{"d":"युधि:","m":"war"},{"d":"स्थातुम्","m":"to stand"},{"d":"नशक्ताः","m":"not possible."}]},{"v":17,"dev":"अयंचराजाव्यसनाभिभूतोमित्रैरमित्रप्रतिमैर्भवद्भि: ।अन्वास्यतेराक्षसनाशनार्थेतीक्ष्णःप्रकृत्याह्यसीक्षयकारी","trans":"\"This king who is by nature violent and acts without thinking about being an addict to seven vices, is destroying Rakshasas. You are also attending to him calling yourself as friends but like enemies.\"","words":[{"d":"व्यसनाभिभूतः","m":"one who is a slave to vices"},{"d":"प्रकृत्या:","m":"by nature"},{"d":"तीक्ष्णः","m":"violent in action"},{"d":"असमीक्षयकारी:","m":"one who does without thinking"},{"d":"अयंराजा:","m":"this king,अमित्रप्रतिमैः like enemies"},{"d":"मित्रैः","m":"friends"},{"d":"भवद्भि:","m":"you also"},{"d":"राक्षसनाशनार्थे:","m":"for the destruction of Rakshasas"},{"d":"अन्वास्यते:","m":"attending. Vices The seven vices are harshness in speech, harshness in punishment, extravagance, drinking, weakness for women, hunting and gambling."}]},{"v":18,"dev":"अनन्तभोगेनसहस्रमूर्थ्नानागेनभीमेनमहाबलेव ।बलात्परिक्षिप्तमिमंभवन्तोराजानमुत्क्षिप्यविमोचयन्तु","trans":"\"This king is entwined by a fearsome and extremely strong thousand hooded snake endowed with extraordinary energy at present. Lift him up and relieve him.\"","words":[{"d":"अनन्तभोगेन","m":"endowed with extraordinary energy"},{"d":"सहस्रमूर्द्ना","m":"with thousand heads"},{"d":"महाबलेन","m":"by extremely strong"},{"d":"भीमेन","m":"fearsome"},{"d":"नागेन","m":"snake"},{"d":"बलात्","m":"with strength,परिक्षिप्तम् is entwined with"},{"d":"इमंराजानम्","m":"this king"},{"d":"भवन्तः","m":"for the present time"},{"d":"उत्क्षिप्य:","m":"lift up"},{"d":"विमोचयन्तु","m":"relieve."}]},{"v":19,"dev":"यावद्धिकेशग्रहणातसुहृद्भि: समेत्यसर्वैःपरिपूर्णकामैः ।निगृह्यराजापरिरक्षितव्योभूतैर्यथाभीमबलैर्गृहीतः","trans":"\"The king will have to be protected by all friends joined together whose wishes have been gratified even by catching him by his hair forcibly just as a man surrounded by a devil of terrific strength is pulled out by his hair.\"","words":[{"d":"परिपूर्णकामैः","m":"whose wishes have been gratified"},{"d":"सर्वैः","m":"all"},{"d":"सुहृद्भि:","m":"friends also"},{"d":"समेत्य:","m":"joined together राजा: king"},{"d":"भीमबलैः","m":"of terrific strength"},{"d":"भूतै:","m":"by devils"},{"d":"गृहीतःयथा:","m":"just as"},{"d":"केशग्रहणात् यावत्","m":"even catching him by hair"},{"d":"निगृह्य:","m":"by force"},{"d":"परिरक्षितव्यःहि:","m":"will have to be protected."}]},{"v":20,"dev":"सुवारिणाराघवसागरेणप्रच्छाद्यमानस्तरसाभवद्भि: ।युक्तस्त्वयंतारयितुंसमेत्यकाकुत्स्थपातालमुखेपतन्सः","trans":"\"He is going to fall into the ocean called Rama to be destroyed, engulfed in the pit of the shape of Kakutstha Rama, the underworld. It is proper for all of us to join and make him free.\"","words":[{"d":"सुवारिणा:","m":"into the pit"},{"d":"राघवसागरेण:","m":"ocean called Raghava"},{"d":"तरसा:","m":"to be destroyed"},{"d":"प्रच्छाद्यमानः","m":"engulfed"},{"d":"काकुत्स्थ:","m":"Kakutstha's"},{"d":"पातालमुखे:","m":"the underworld"},{"d":"पतन्","m":"fall into"},{"d":"अयम्","m":"us"},{"d":"भवद्भि:","m":"at present"},{"d":"समेत्य:","m":"joined together"},{"d":"तारयितुम्","m":"will have to make him free"},{"d":"युक्तः","m":"proper for you."}]},{"v":21,"dev":"इदंपुरस्यास्यसराक्षसस्यराज्ञश्चपथ्यंससुहृज्जनस्य ।सम्यग्घिवाक्यंस्वमतंब्रवीमिनरेन्द्रपुत्रायददामपत्नीम्","trans":"\"I tell these good words embodying my opinion. Let the king's wife be given away for the good of the Rakshasas, their dear ones, for the capital and the king.\"","words":[{"d":"सराक्षसस्य:","m":"for the Rakshasas"},{"d":"अस्य:","m":"there"},{"d":"पुरस्य:","m":"capital"},{"d":"ससुहृज्जनस्य:","m":"for all of you the dear ones"},{"d":"राज्ञश्च:","m":"for the king"},{"d":"पथ्यम्:","m":"embodying"},{"d":"स्वमतम्","m":"my opinion"},{"d":"इदंवाक्यम्","m":"these words"},{